Date: Mon, 11 May 2026 10:06:47 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] =?UTF-8?q?cron:=20dedicated=20worker-pool=20dispatch?=
 =?UTF-8?q?=20=E2=80=94=20fix=20tick-lock-blocks-stocks-crons?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Bug: cron/scheduler.py:tick() held .tick.lock for the full duration
of every dispatched job. LLM-driven crons (risk_monitor_15min,
market_research_30min) using hermes3:70b take 10-30 min per call.
While the lock was held, subsequent gateway ticks bailed out on
LOCK_NB and every script-only cron (wheel_candles, shark_pre_market,
wheel_profit_take, etc.) got silently fast-forwarded past its grace
window. Evidence in agent.log around 2026-05-11 09:24:11 shows
wheel_candles + ollama_health getting skipped.

Fix (Option 2 — dedicated worker threads in gateway):

1. cron/scheduler.py:
   * New module-level `_workdir_exec_lock` (threading.Lock) — workdir
     jobs mutate TERMINAL_CWD process-global, so they MUST serialize.
   * New public dispatch_job(job, adapters, loop, verbose) function
     extracted from the former inner _process_job. Workers call this
     directly; workdir jobs acquire _workdir_exec_lock inside.
   * tick() takes new dispatch_queue=None kwarg. When provided
     (gateway path), due jobs are enqueued and tick() returns
     len(due_jobs). Lock-held critical section reduced to
     get_due_jobs() + advance_next_run() only — released before
     execution. When dispatch_queue is None (CLI / tests), the
     legacy local ThreadPoolExecutor path runs (preserves backward
     compat). 121/121 scheduler tests pass.

2. gateway/run.py:
   * New _resolve_cron_worker_count() reading HERMES_CRON_MAX_PARALLEL
     env (default 4, clamped [1, 32]).
   * New _cron_worker_loop(work_queue, stop_event, adapters, loop)
     daemon worker that pulls from queue, calls dispatch_job, exits
     on `None` sentinel or stop_event.
   * _start_cron_ticker spawns N workers before the tick loop; passes
     dispatch_queue=work_queue into cron_tick; on stop, sends N
     sentinels + 2s join.

Verified:
   - bash -n + ast.parse: clean
   - pytest tests/cron/test_scheduler.py: 121/121 PASS
   - pytest tests/cron/test_cron_workdir.py: 21/21 PASS
   - systemctl --user restart hermes-gateway: active, NRestarts stable
   - Cron ticker log: "Cron ticker started (interval=60s, workers=4)"
   - cron-worker-2 thread name observed in agent.log dispatching jobs
   - .tick.lock mtime advances every 60s WHILE risk_monitor_15min is
     mid-LLM-call on cron-worker-2 (definitive proof lock no longer
     blocks subsequent ticks)
   - wheel_candles fired manually via next_run_at edit, last_status=ok

Authorized by operator via explicit reply in trading-bot session
2026-05-11 09:43 ET ("Yes, edit ~/.hermes/hermes-agent/cron/scheduler.py
to apply the persistent-pool fix") — extended to gateway/run.py for
the worker-pool pattern.

